SmartTip.Title: Recycling Process
SmartTip.Content: Add food scraps for up to 7 days or until the bin is full! The recycling process can be run at any time.

SmartTip.Title: Kitchen Placement
SmartTip.Content: The food recycler may be located at any convenient location in the home. It has been designed to fit at the end of the kitchen counter or island.

SmartTip.Title: Child Safety
SmartTip.Content: The food recycler should be used only by adults. If there are children in the home, lock the food recycler lid at all times.

SmartTip.Title: Acceptable Compost
SmartTip.Content: Do not put large pits, large bones, shells or flammable liquids in your food recycler.

SmartTip.Title: Use it Later
SmartTip.Content: If you don’t want to use your output material right away, you can store it in an airtight container.

SmartTip.Title: Cleaning Food Jam
SmartTip.Content: If there is a food waste jam, use a spatula or wooden spoon to stir the food around the mixing blades in the food bin to free the jam.

SmartTip.Title: External Cleaning
SmartTip.Content: Use cleaning wipes to regularly clean the outside of your food recycler.

SmartTip.Title: Dishwasher Safe
SmartTip.Content: The funnel is removable and is dishwasher safe. It can also be cleaned by warm and soapy water.
